last_episode_to_air.name: Barking Up the Wrong Tree
last_episode_to_air.overview: The fate of the human race is hanging in the balance, and Earth's not gonna save itself. Time for a good old-fashioned dogfight!

name: Dogs in Space
overview: In the not-so-distant future, genetically enhanced dogs are sent across the universe in search of a new home for the human race. It’s a giant cosmic game of fetch, as the canines seek a planet that will save humanity and - more importantly - let them return to their beloved owners.
tagline: Fetch — a new planet for us all!

episodes.name: Fetch
episodes.overview: Who let the dogs out — into space? Garbage can't help but disobey after an alien negotiation goes sideways. Yet the next planet looks so promising.

episodes.name: Here, Girl!
episodes.overview: On the planet, Garbage and the crew try to save an angry, capable canine who's gone feral. But who will rescue the rescuers with the Pluto gone?

episodes.name: Spin
episodes.overview: Taming the beast can be tough. Kira faces her great fear: brunch. Meanwhile, Garbage must jump through the hoops of Penelope's training scenarios.

episodes.name: Who's a Good Boy?
episodes.overview: Unleashed, the Pluto team explores a planet that might be perfect for humanity. But something — or someone — stinks. Also, Loaf must take the lead.

episodes.name: Settle Down
episodes.overview: Awww-some and then some: The cute ― and chaos ― factor rockets out of control when Stella discovers that her crewmates have turned into puppies.

episodes.name: Speak
episodes.overview: Which comes first: a seed or a world? Dogs or humans? After failing to talk an alien into handing over planet-saving seed, the crew attempts a heist.

episodes.name: Stay
episodes.overview: Love hurts. Garbage and the team stumble on a world that seems to be populated by their beloved owners. But what are these odd shape-shifters hiding?

episodes.name: Watch Me
episodes.overview: In it to win it. Eager to compete in a mech war, Chonies looks to Garbage for help. But he's been pulled into Kira's plan to change canine minds.

episodes.name: Leave It
episodes.overview: Opposites attract... or not. Garbage and Happy must work together if they want to avoid disaster on a magnetic planet. Elsewhere, Kira goes on the run.

episodes.name: Drop It
episodes.overview: Dogfight! When a pooch goes rogue, two rival crews battle as one. They must fight to get back to the base, save the mission ― and more.

episodes.name: Galactic Tactics
episodes.overview: Captain Stella makes her first big call by choosing a new tactical officer. But when the crew embarks on its next mission, there's a stowaway on board.

episodes.name: Who's a Tea Boy?
episodes.overview: Garbage takes a job at a tea shop, where the day-to-day isn't nearly as exciting as fighting aliens and pulling evasive maneuvers... until it is.

episodes.name: Who Wants a Treaty?
episodes.overview: An extra-large planet checks lots of boxes for the team — but only if they can successfully negotiate to share it with an alien species.

episodes.name: Paws & Rewind
episodes.overview: Pepper builds a high-tech simulator to predict the crew's behavior in any scenario. But is it really paws-sible to predict the future?

episodes.name: Mistaken IdEDity
episodes.overview: Ed's bad habit of pinning his crimes on unsuspecting crew mates catches up with him when Chonies is wrongfully kidnapped by an alien thief.

episodes.name: Let There Be Loaf
episodes.overview: When space pirates threaten the M-Bark, it's up to an anxious Loaf — the least likely dog to be a hero — to step up, face his fears and save the day.

episodes.name: Freeze Out
episodes.overview: During an icy rescue mission on a distant planet, a series of flashbacks reveal that longtime enemies Happy and Garbage actually used to be friends.

episodes.name: Garbage's Horrorscope
episodes.overview: Garbage's former mentor has the power to win Garbage his captain's badge back by taking it away from Stella — but that isn't what Garbage wants!

episodes.name: No Good Seed Goes Unpunished
episodes.overview: A guilt-ridden Garbage comes clean to Stella, unaware that plantlike aliens are plotting revenge on dogs and humans for past wrongs.

episodes.name: Barking Up the Wrong Tree
episodes.overview: The fate of the human race is hanging in the balance, and Earth's not gonna save itself. Time for a good old-fashioned dogfight!
